review_title: Overall, the facilities were very good--clean, comfortable room and common areas.
good_review: The rooms were very clean which is probably the most important aspect for me when traveling. The housekeeping staff was very friendly and accommodating. I also liked the wonderful couch in the room with the two ottomans. It was so refreshing to have a comfortable place to watch TV and work on the computer. It also had the right amount of facilities in the lobby--a pleasant bar, sufficient tables to get together to talk, a business/work area, and a small snack/grocery store.
bad_review:
The breakfast was awful. The bagels tasted like paper, and there weren't really other options for a bread. A few muffins, different types of bread, maybe some Danish or croissants would have helped. We didn't bother after the first day; it was that bad. It could have been open a bit later as well.
Another problem--no available coffee after breakfast. Just having the coffee and real cream available all day makes a huge difference!
Paying for parking is the one thing that would deter us from coming back.

good_review:
I liked that the property was close to my venue and it had a balcony to allow air to circulate. 
The staff is fantastic. See below!
bad_review:
I did not like the lack of attention to the elevator. It was down for two days, which allowed for only one elevator. This hotel is very busy, and having one elevator was inconvenient. But, I can live with that. 
What really sent me to a boil is a guest below decided to disregard the one courteous rule of pretty much EVERY hotel in the world—smoking!! The signs are all over the place, even marked on the slider towards the balcony and, yes, even ON the balcony! So, the disgusting plume of smoke wafted in my room above him. 
But, this is the redeeming part: I called the front desk, they promptly—I mean promptly— called the room and told the tenants that smoking is prohibited in the rooms and that there are designated smoking areas outside the hotel. Furthermore, they called me back and said if they continued, they would be told to leave! 
No more smoke for the remainder of my stay and I got to enjoy the fresh air from the balcony. 
Now, that’s service!!!

review_title: Impressive hotel with a large, clean room and amazing view, in a wonderful area
good_review:
This was probably one of the best hotels I have ever stayed at, especially for a major city. I am so so happy we chose this hotel over some other options in the more touristy areas. 
- The area is wonderful. No, it's not what many guidebooks will recommend for first-time tourists to San Francisco, but I PROMISE it is better than staying in Fisherman's Wharf or Union Square. The area feels really safe, is super close to ANY public transit you could need (it's literally just outside the door), and is a wonderful place to walk around and explore, with many nice restaurants and coffee shops. Could not say better things about the area for a traveler. 
- The hotel itself is very impressive. The lobby is beautiful and the elevators are beautiful and exciting! They were working on a gorgeous Christmas display while we were there. 
- The room was large especially for a city, very clean, and we fortunately booked a room with a balcony, and OMG, what an amazing view. 
I highly recommend staying here for visits to San Francisco!

good_review: What is there not to like about the HYATT. It is always a wonderful hotel to stay at. My wife fell in love with the balcony with the bay view room. It is the only one we get. The staff are warm and welcoming from the valet drivers outside/entrance greeters are friendly,funny and professional. Every question i had they were mainly the ones to answer it for me. The front desk service had great customer service. They greeted me with a warm welcome to the establishment and because it was valentines day they had a beautiful red rose for my lady and champagne in the room. It made my wife feel special that day which they did all of it. Walking to my room I was even greeted by one of the service men. We had a little chat with laughter at the end, he saw me and my wife kind of struggling with our suitcases and even offered to help. I thought that was genuine for a worker that probably didn't even get paid to that job. So for the managers to the people in charge/owners of the facility. The front desk workers are awesome, but give a BIG notice and thank you to your workers that probably don't get the love and respect they should. And that is your frontline/entrance workers with amazing attitudes and knowledge for us/guest. The workers that are in the back stage that keep the place clean and in working order maid/handyman. They alone would be one reason I would come back to this hotel. Which I have numerous of times. So I hope you do something special for those workers that don't get the recognition that they deserve. Thank you all staff members for making my wife's valentines day one for the books. Facebook/Instagram friends and family wifes will be jealous on this one. Thank you for making me look like the dopest husband this year. Now tell your boss to throw you a LITTLE SOMETHING 😉 💰
bad_review:
The location can be difficult to find. If I was new to san francisco 
And didn't know my way around. It can be confusing to find the hotel at night on a busy,crowded, rainy day. The parking garage is even more confusing. You are going into another building that is not even connected to the hotel. So when you pick lobby it takes you to a office lobby and not your hotel. I asked the lady/ security do I check in here. Looking at me confused she said you must be looking for the hotel. She then instructed me to go back in the elevator and go one floor down to the "streets". Once that elevator opens you are half way there. You are then walking across the way which is outside to get to the main entrance/ valet. Having a girl that over packs her life lol, has to have three to five suitcases and travel bags. Then my 4 four year old stuff. So the parking and location is all the negative thing I have to say.

review_title: While the hotel's location was great, the outdated rooms, unresponsive staff, and lack of parking options left me di
good_review:
Location. 
Some of the staff were so nice.. most are not.
bad_review:
My recent stay at the hotel was not as pleasant as I had hoped, despite its prime location. The surroundings were fantastic, but the accommodations themselves left much to be desired. The rooms appeared slightly outdated and in need of refurbishment, which did not justify the high price tag.
Furthermore, the staff’s lack of responsiveness was a significant issue, and i felt that sometime that they need to learn how to act nice.
Adding to my dissatisfaction was the lack of parking facilities for guests. There were no on-site parking options, and I had to resort to a nearby parking lot, which charged an exorbitant fee of nearly $40 per night. The distance between the parking lot and the hotel was quite a walk, making it inconvenient, especially when carrying luggage or returning late in the evening. (They wont help you to bring your luggage from the car!).

acommodation: Habitación con cama extragrande.
review_title: Sehr gutes Hotel mit Spitzenlage und toller Aussicht.
good_review: Sehr großes, modern eingerichtetes, sauberes Zimmer mit Panoramafenster. Blick war zur Market-Street und auf die Bay-Bridge (12. Stock). Bett war King-size mit vier großen Kopfkissen. Neben normalen Lampen gibt es ein Ambient-Light über dem Bett. Toll: Wenn man nachts im Dunkeln aufsteht, registriert ein Sensor unter dem Bett die Bewegungen und es aktiviert ein kleines Licht unter dem Bett (aber nur auf der Seite, wo man aufgestanden ist), sodass man nirgendwo anstößt. Das Bad und die Dusche sind sehr groß, sauber und sehr gut beleuchtet. Das Hotel-Atrium, die 'Außenlifte' und der Blick von dort sowie von den einzelnen Etagen (immerhin 17) auf den 'Innenhof' ist sehr beeindruckend. Man sollte aber keine Höhenangst haben.
bad_review: Die Fenster sind einfach verglast und deshalb nicht sehr schalldicht. Desweiteren heizen sie sich im Sommer sehr schnell in der Sonne auf und damit auch das Zimmer, sodass die Klimaanlage permanent an ist und (vergeblich) versucht, die gewünschte Temperatur einzustellen.

good_review:

Die Zimmer sind geräumig, auch zu viert und wir hatten einen tollen Blick aufs Meer.
Die Architektur des Atriums ist toll, dort hat es praktische Aufenthaltsmöglichkeiten und einen Concierge welcher sehr freundlich war und uns gute Tipps gegeben hat und auch direkt Buchungen vorgenommen hat. Wir hatten einmal das Frühstücksbuffet, etwas teuer, aber sehr reichhaltig, abwechslungsreich und sehr fein.
bad_review: Die unteren Stockwerke waren grad im Umbau, daher war es werktags im Atrium zum Teil etwas lärmig.

acommodation: Habitación con 2 camas grandes
good_review: Colazione a pagamento ma comunque con ampia scelta. Personale molto gentile e sempre pronto a soddisfare le varie richieste. Posizione molto buona a 10 metri dall’embarcadero . Tutto il personale si è dimostrato molto cortese sempre pronto ad accoglierti con un sorriso. Camera a due letti molto ampia moderna e con un bel bagno con vasca e doccia . Pulizia ottima. Albergo un po’ caro ma con un ottimo rapporto qualità prezzo.Lo consiglio.

acommodation: Habitación con ducha adaptada para personas con discapacidad - 2 camas grandes
review_title: Schönes Hotel weitab vom Trubel des Piers
good_review:
Tolle, moderne und große Zimmer mit 2 riesigen Betten. Toll ausgestattet und eine sehr schöne Lobby & Aufteilung der Zimmer generell. Uns hat auch sehr gut gefallen das der Wasch & Duschbereich noch durch eine Zwischentür getrennt war. Dadurch hörte man auch nichts vom Flur, wenn mal Leute vorbeiliefen. 
Außerdem tolle Lage direkt gegenüber vom San Francisco Ferry Building & dadurch viele Essmöglichkeiten. Und ein super Ausblick jeden Morgen!
bad_review:
Es ist relativ weit ab vom Schuss und in SFO ist es sehr schwer sich via Uber etc. fortzubewegen, es sei denn man möchte viel Geld ausgeben :D Wir hatten also jedes Mal einen ca. 30 minütigen Fußweg zum Pier 39 und Fisherman’s Wharf. 
Die Straße beim Hotel ist sehr laut und man hört sie noch deutlich in den Zimmern. Das sollte man sich bei Buchung bewusst sein und ggf. Ohropax parat haben, wenn man da empfindlich ist wie ich :) 
Wir hatten extra um ein ruhiges Zimmer gebeten und dafür auch extra bezahlt, allerdings nützte das nichts. Außerdem war direkt unter unserem Zimmer eine Bar, die einen Abend wirklich extrem laut war. Gott sei Dank wurde sie aber um 22:00 Uhr geschlossen, sodass es uns nicht die ganze Nacht wachhielt. Das sind aber Faktoren, die das Hotelpersonal nicht beeinflussen kann :)

acommodation: Habitación con cama extragrande.
bad_review:
Для отеля уровня Hyatt это довольно печально. В ванной нет тапок, халата, крема для тела. На потолке висят волосы…
В номере даже нет питьевой воды, впервые с таким сталкиваюсь.
Шумоизоляция с улицы практически отсутствует.
На паркинге, который стоит $80 нам сказали, что они не несут ответственности за электро-велосипед, прикрепленный к авто. На вопрос что нам делать и как в таком случае они несут ответственность за машину, сотрудники пожали плечами и порекомендовали забрать велик в номер!! В итоге пыльный, грязный велосипед пришлось ставить в нашем номере. Всё это очень плохо. Мы выбирали эту сеть, так как доверяем ей и в других странах не было проблема с этим отелями, но тут сплошное разочарование.

bad_review: Trotz Zimmer im 17. Stock recht laut (Musik von draußen, Fahrstuhl und AC). Badezimmer ein wenig in die Jahre gekommen. Keine Flasche Wasser auf dem Zimmer. Zudem habe ich keine Info zu den in der Buchung genannten Benefits erhalten.

review_title: Это самый ужасный Hyatt в котором я когда либо жил. Полный ужас.
bad_review: Отель грязный и старый. Ковролин в номере весь в пятнах и грязный. Канализация забитая и вода не уходит. В номере воняет сыростью. Мебель старая. Минибар пустой (воду хотя бы положили жлобы). WiFi 24$ в сутки - жесть, уже во всем мире и даже в Тель-Авиве в Hyatt интернет бесплатный. На балконе были окурки и балкон никто не убирает. Персонал не компетентный. В период Ковида ограничили сервисы (завтраков, парковки, бэлбой). Почему в период Ковида нельзя воспользоваться паркингом отеля, а надо ставить автомобиль в паркинге торгового центра сотрудники не могут пояснить. Самый УЖАСНЫЙ отель Hyatt!!!
